Pre-Game Insights: Memphis Grizzlies and Milwaukee Bucks are set to play in a non-conference matchup on November 1, 2024.
Memphis Grizzlies finished the 2023-24 season with a 27-55 overall record and a 9-32 record at home.
Milwaukee Bucks finished the 2023-24 season with a 49-33 overall record, 34-18 in Eastern Conference action, and 18-22 on the road.
Grizzlies averaged 105.8 points per game while shooting 43.5% from the field and 34.6% from deep last season.
Bucks gave up 116.4 points per game while committing 19.2 fouls last season.

Injuries for the Grizzlies include Ja Morant (day to day, thigh), John Konchar (day to day, foot), Luke Kennard (out, foot), Zach Edey (day to day, calf), Vince Williams Jr. (out, leg), GG Jackson II (out, foot), and Cam Spencer (out, ankle).
Injury for the Bucks includes Khris Middleton (day to day, ankle).
